<br>
There is a lot of RL that needs my attention. Playing this wonderful game took too much time. Finding groups was painful when I hit the 50's. Joining a guild helped but became another time commitment. Grinding for exp was so slow. I am just disappointed that I did not see all the zones, planes, and mobs. I have been playing this game off and on for the past 2 years. I still had fun but once away from the monitor I was disappointed that I did not spend those 2 to 6 hours doing something more constructive.<br>
<br>
I remember first entering the game and choosing a high elf wizard, running to the guards when those dangerous bats in G Fay had me down to 1/2 heal. Someone gave me 4pp and a backpack with some fish and water, and I thought I was rich. Before the level 10?-lose no exp or loot patch, I was so frantic about finding my body in G Fay with my meager items that I was so grateful when someone helped me locate my corpse. I fell off Kelethin once and that was enough. SoW fading, when a train ran by in Crush Bone, meant you would see your bind point real soon. Finding out that the guards will not help you when the faeries are beating your ass was a hoot. I never attacked a faerie again.<br>
<br>
I have come to this site for the past two years and only started contributing posts in the past 4 months or so. Thank you to those who have shared their knowledge and experience with all of us who read this site.<br>
<br>
May you overflow with mana and your evac spell never fizzle.<br>
<br>
Gorblast 52, 255int, 2AA<br>
Agnostic<br>
Quellious<br>
